---
const foundations = [
  { label: "FAQ", href: "/faqs", external: false },
  { label: "Vision paper", href: "#", external: false },
  { label: "Briefs", href: "#", external: false },
  { label: "QBI study — tadpole", href: "#", external: false },
  {
    label: "PMC: Quantum biology review",
    href: "https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6304024/",
    external: true,
  },
  {
    label: "SciAm: Bird navigation",
    href: "https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/how-migrating-birds-use-quantum-effects-to-navigate/",
    external: true,
  },
  { label: "TBD", href: "#", external: false },
  { label: "TBD", href: "#", external: false },
];
---

<section class="bg-plum-darkest text-cream py-20 md:py-24">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6">A brief history</h2>
    <p
      class="max-w-4xl font-sans text-base text-cream/80 leading-relaxed mb-14"
    >
      Soon after the birth of quantum physics in the 1920s and 30s, scientists
      began searching for ways to apply quantum ideas in biology. Erwin
      Schrödinger, one of the fathers of quantum theory, wrote "What is Life?"
      in 1944, postulating the need for quantum mechanics to explain heredity,
      prior to the discovery of DNA. In the 1960s and 70s, researchers began
      finding examples of natural phenomena, including tunneling in enzymes and
      bird navigation, which depended on quantum phenomena. Now, researchers are
      aiming to construct new instruments to directly probe quantum states and
      help unlock the quantum secrets of life.
    </p>

    <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-cream mb-6">
      Explore the foundations
    </h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
      {
        foundations.map((f) => (
          <a
            href={f.href}
            target={f.external ? "_blank" : undefined}
            rel={f.external ? "noopener noreferrer" : undefined}
            class="group flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 rounded-full bg-mauve/30 border border-cream/15 text-cream font-sans text-sm hover:bg-mauve/50 transition-colors text-center"
          >
            <span>{f.label}</span>
            {f.external && (
              <svg
                width="12"
                height="12"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.5"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                class="opacity-70 group-hover:opacity-100 shrink-0"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6" />
                <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9" />
                <line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3" />
              </svg>
            )}
          </a>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
